description:
The Saint of Killers makes his way across the ocean and Starr finds himself entertaining two extremely unwelcome guests--a very special little boy and Allfather D'Aronique, the unbelievably gruesome head of the Grail.

The Allfather comes to Masada, wondering what Starr has been up to; Cassidy is tortured by Frankie the Eunuch; Jesse slips away from Tulip, fearing for her safety.
name: Stormbringers (Crusaders Part 3)
Who Dies With the Most Toys...

description: Arrested by the New York police for the murder of a young coed, Polish pilot Janos Prohaska--the Blackhawk--faces certain death unless the Golden Age Sandman can help prove his innocence and find the real killer without revealing Prohaska's secret mission in America. "The Blackhawk" part 2.
name: The Blackhawk: Act II of IV

description: Part 13 of 14. The National Interest now controls the power of both the American talisman and the Spear of Destiny. Can even the Spectre hope to defeat them now?
name: In Dark Defeat

description:
Demon Quest: Part Three of Three

Trapped in a Wild West version of Hell, Matt O'Dare, the Shade and Jack Knight must defeat the Poster Demon to free the souls of its victims. With the Shade rendered powerless and the Star Staff drained of its cosmic energy, the gamble grows dire as the three realize their very souls are on the line.

Jack arrives to a sight in Hell. Matt O'dare chased by demon cowboys. The Shade dressed all in white.

And the demon.
name: To Hell and Back, Conclusion

description: The “Plus Specials“ continue, teaming your favorite DC heroes! Captain Marvel Jr. and Superboy are drawn into a web of danger by a mysterious foe, and all hell breaks loose when the two super-powered teens find themselves battling Superman and Captain Marvel!
name: Plus the Power of Shazam!

description: Superman tries to learn more about his home planet of Krypton, but gets interrupted when Metropolis strikes a case of serious bad luck--in the form of hundreds of robot black cats attacking the city!
name: Distant Thunder

description: When bored heiress Barbara Gordon meets free-spirited circus daredevil Dick Grayson, sparks fly right from the start, leading to a scandalous romance and the reckless decision to become costumed adventurers Batgirl and Robin on the rooftops of Gotham City! But mere mischief becomes serious business when Dick's family is murdered, and Batgirl and Robin set out to mete justice on the Graysons' killers. At the same time, Detective Bruce Wayne is on the job to take down the young thrill-seekers and solve the mystery of the Grayson murders.
name: Thrillkiller

description: Earth's fate is in the hands of Wonder Woman and Officer Mike Schorr as they come up against the final stages of the Earth Movers plans.
name: The Men Who Moved the World

description: The two universes are back to the way they should be. Access is enjoying a nice carriage ride in central park with his girlfriend, Ming. Suddenly, Access is confronted by Jubilee. During time that the Marvel and the DC universes began to merge she had run into Robin and had developed a thing for him. She convinces Access to take her to the DC universe so that she could see him.
name: Two Sides of the Same Coin

description:
The issue begins with Jenny Romano waking up Jackie, who finds himself sleeping in the garbage at the back of the bar where Jenny works at. He comes inside and is offered coffee, but soon starts seeing a Darkling on his drink's reflection and walks out of the bar desperately. Sonatine is seen at this time planning to meet Jackie Estacado, as his first attempt to do so was foiled. Uncle Frankie is in the hospital, recovering from the attack last issue where Jackie observes him, before pondering going to liberty due to what one of the members of the Brotherhood of Darkness told him after the attack. He arrives in the island and is rendered unconscious by the Brotherhood, who then bring him to their underground base. The leader, Sonatine introduces himself to Jackie and explains some of the story behind The Darkness and The Angelus. Sonatine wants to use Jackie for the Brotherhood, however Jackie refuses this offer and a physical altercation ensues, which Jackie easily wins.

Back at the bar Jackie is seen with Jenny drinking and soon picks up a woman who he brings home in a cab. Sonatine then arrives in the bar a moment too late and when he finds out what happens from Jenny, he wants to stop Jackie from going home with the woman as soon as he can.
name: Underworld

description: Daniel is one of many mental patients under the care of Christina a young intern at a dark and foreboding mental institution. Daniel has secrets that he is either unable or unwilling to share, and Christina wants desperately for him to share them so he can heal mentally.
name: A Kairos Moment

description: Although extremely traumatized, Forsberg, the military strategist, is successfully transported to Spawn's alley for safekeeping until Terry and Al figure out how to use him to their advantage against Wynn. When Cy-Gor makes a surprise attack on Spawn, Forsberg huddles in the background watching the battle. He then returns to reality with some startling information about Cy-Gor's origin and connection to Wynn.
name: The Beast

description: Elektra deals with the guilt over letting Nina's parents die. Nina gets caught up with some criminals with ulterior motives, but Elektra intervenes just in time. Meanwhile the Architect continues unfolding his plan.
name: I Know How You Feel

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
The very first appearance of the Thunderbolts!

With the general public still unknown of the team's true identities, the Thunderbolts try to win over the public by setting out to capture the Hulk. They find him in a rodeo. However The Hulk, manages to escape by destroying a dam forcing the Thunderbolts to save the people and town from destruction,enabling the Hulk to escape but not before their actions are filmed by the spectators.
name: Introducing the Thunderbolts!

description: The Trapster
name: A Matter Of Respect

description: In this story a new Hobgoblin is introduced. But - he claims to be the first Hobgoblin and kills the one who in his opinion doesn't deserve this identity: Jason Macendale!
name: Victims

description:
Omega Squadron is on leave.  The girls spend their time in Sydney, Australia and get into a bar fight.  Matt Decker hangs out with his friend Yoshi Mishima and Nog goes through goes through Matt's stuff while he was gone and discovers Matt's huge collection of Marvel Comics. Nog however opens and reads them all without taking care of the three hundred year old books.  In the long run however Matt and Nog become closer friends even if Matt won't admit it.
 
Flashback
In a flashback T'Priell relives a time as a young woman when she tries to go out in the wilderness with nothing but her logic and a small knife.  She is not really able to find out how she would do because her father Telark intervenes and they are both nearly killed in the drama that takes place in the drama afterwards.
name: Liberty
Action Of The Tiger; The Unkindest Cut

description: Concluding an all-new three-part thriller! The crew thought they were being nice when they rescued the helpless Talaxians. Well, it looks like the Talaxians weren't so helpless! You got it, they're mercenary agents of the Trabe, who happen to have a gigantic ship waiting to take out our heroes!
name: Repercussions
What If... Starring Wolverine - A Man No More

description:
Cresting the Trudd wall was no mean feat but the view is amazing as the team find their way off the island is a bridge in the Moonguzzit sea. Once again Akiko dreams are of Alia Rellapor and of conversing with Poog in his own language. 
 
Spukler's ingenious idea saves the crew a lot of time and they start to enter the realm of Alia Rellapor 
 
Bonus Story: Movie Mayhem
An old enemy kidnaps the girls of the team...to deliver them to an even worse villain.

name: Finder

description:
Aquaman enlists the Martian Manhunter's aid to force his will on the Cybernetic Entity.

Aquaman and Dolphin meet with a man in a dark alley in long trench coats where Aquaman seeks his aid, but with him refusing. He then reveals his true form of The Martian Manhunter following a comment by Dolphin, but spurs him to agree to help on the condition he is not required to attack Japan directly. Meanwhile in Japan Demon Gate and his brother meet with the prime minister of Japan who is scolding him for his carelessness of dragging them into his personal vendetta. Aquaman then reveals his need for the Manhunter, to help him retake the floating Poseidonis which proves very difficult when the city attacks them, but Manhunter eventually manages to break through the main gates.

Aquaman with the manhunter's aid then manages to gain dominion over the sentience in the ship. Meanwhile in the ocean Deep Blue leads the Sea Devils deep to the ocean's floor, where they find a dead dinosaur which has been there for less then a week. While Aquaman has moved Poseidonis over the streets of Tokyo calling for Demon Gate to be turned over to him. His brother then brings him to the roof where he disables his body leaving him for Aquaman who takes him back to Poseidonis placing him on trial. Aquaman then deems him guilty despite Dolphin and Nemek's urging that it isn't what Porm would want, with all the sea life telling him otherwise Aquaman commutes Demon Gate's sentence sentencing him to an island with no weapons, to be brought food by the local sea life daily.
name: Setting Sun

description:
A group of aliens calling themselves the Hyperclan come to Earth professing to be galactic saviors. Having witnessed their home world suffer great ecological destruction, they seek to prevent the same thing from happening on other worlds. The general populace of Earth immediately ingratiate themselves to the Hyperclan, but members of the super-hero community have concerns over the team's seeming generosity. To demonstrate their pledge to heal the Earth, the Hyperclan use their powers to turn the barren Sahara Desert into a veritable Eden.

The Hyperclan also lend their power to the cause of law enforcement. However, instead of incarcerating criminals, they execute them. This is also supported by the general public.

Before long though, the Hyperclan begin to take offensive action against those who might threaten their goals; specifically the Justice League. The Hyperclan ambush the League aboard their satellite, completely tearing through the sides of the structure. The escape shuttle pods are useless so Metamorpho encases the entire team and jettisons himself from the satellite before it explodes entirely. The League members survive the planet fall to Earth, but they all suffer severe injuries. Metamorpho is rendered inert, possibly dead. Afterward,Protex, leader of the Hyperclan erects a watchtower structure in the icy plains of Antarctica named Z'onn Z'orr.

Earth's most potent super-heroes meet up at the old League Secret Society in Rhode Island. Realizing that the Hyperclan are a threat, they discuss new strategies. Batman arrives and tells them to prepare for war.
name: Them!

description:
Cable, Domino and Garrison Kane are in the Microverse, teamed with the Micronauts, on a mission to rescue Copycat from Psycho-Man. They have breached the villain's fortress, but Kane, under the influence of a hate beam, attacks Cable. Despite Domino's protests, the team leaves the overwhelmed Cable to be captured by Psycho-Man, while Commander Rann formulates a plan. The group breaks into a lab where Rann, Mari and Bug can reduce their size.

The miniaturized trio enter Psycho-Man's Body Banks through a vent. There they find Kane bound to a device meant to extract his bionics, along with a catatonic Copycat and a weakened Cable. The Micronauts attack Psycho-Man and damage his emotion-simulator while Domino revives Copycat.

As the heroes gain back their abilities, Cable telepathically and telekinetically subdues Psycho-Man.

Having returned to San Francisco, Domino and Copycat make amends, then the latter and Kane leave for parts unknown. Meanwhile, at the Xavier Institute, an unattended communication panel receives a distress call for Cable from Moira MacTaggert in Scotland.
name: All Things Great and Small

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Deadpool takes on a mission to Antarctica, where he finds himself face to face with Sasquatch (Walter Langkowski) of Alpha Flight!!

His assignment is to level a abandoned building, but when setting the device he notices that the station is not so abandoned after all. But, it is too late-the bomb he placed goes off and damages vital equipment. Equipment that pulls Gamma Radiation out of the earth's atmosphere. Now, with the "entire southern hemisphere" in danger, Wilson must battle Sasquatch of Alpha Flight and risk everything to patch the damage he just created.
name: Hey, It's Deadpool! or Deadpool

description: Jenny Sparks reveals her origin to Jackson King.
name: Who Watches the Weatherman?

description: Let's get ready to rrrumblllle!! All hell breaks loose as this gripping yarn rockets to its shattering climax! Shock jock Jerry Delman has lit the fuse -- who will survive the explosion? Frank is missing, Tina's life is in imminent danger, and a frantic Luther plots The Pearl's final demented surprise.

PKNA #2

Due / Two

A mysterious hacker is throwing Duckburg in panic, then Pk decides to investigate: One supply it with the Hall of Total Immersive Interface, in order to inspect the virtual reality. In this non-place, the hacker turns out to be two, the One's backup, made evil by years of inactivity.

PK try to disable Two, but is captured. Everett Ducklair suddenly appears, trying to disable Two with voice code, that was completed by PK when Ducklair is silenced by Two.
name: Due

description: Luse and Cassy discuss the events of the previous issue. Jace and Vido discuss their next move. The return of Tenth and Hyena.
name: Sanctuary Book 4: Strange Days One: No New Tale To Tell

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 4: Strange Days One: No New Tale To Tell

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 4: Strange Days One: No New Tale To Tell

deck: Supergirl battles Chemo, and beats him by convincing him to transform himself into rain.
description: Supergirl visits with Ma and Pa Kent in Kansas, while Chemo rampages across Leesburg in "Chemical Imbalance."
name: Chemical Imbalance

description: Lady Vic, an assassin hired by Angel Marin, came to Bludhaven to collect. Dick got a job as a bartender at a cop bar called Hogan's Alley. Three False Facers with backwards heads - on orders by Soames. Nightwing and Lady Vic both went after Marin's lawyer.
name: Lady be Deadly

description:
As if he didn't cause them enough trouble, Impulse Bart Allen tags along with the Legionnaires in an attempt to join the team.

Impulse visits the Legion, causing chaos in S.T.A.R. Labs and forcing him to team up with the Legion to clean up the mess.
name: Fast Times

description:
Crossovers between the two universes keep happening. The Scorpion attacks Access, Robin and Jubilee in Gotham, but is stopped by Batman, who enables Access to send the Scorpion back to his own universe.

Access enlists the aid of Batman and his detective skills to help figure out what is behind all the crossovers. Clues are put together that implicate Doctor Strange. Batman travels with Access to the Marvel Universe to confront the Doctor. As Doctor Strange and Batman are discussing the problem, Jubilee shows up with the X-men. Arguing and fighting begin. Batman holds his own against the X-Men for a while only to be subdued. At this point Access shows up, (he left during the fighting) with the JLA. The comic ends here to be concluded in # 4.
name: In The Doctor's House

description: "Freakout" part 1, written by Garth Ennis! A man walks into a drug house--and openly shoots eight criminals! When Batman arrives on the scene, he comes face to face with the man and his female partner. Meanwhile, across town, Doctor Freak emerges!
name: Freakout Part 1 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: "Weird Romance" part 1! On what should have been her wedding day, Bridget lies comatose, suspended between life and death. But her real adventure has only just begun. While her fiancé Chris sits by her side, Bridget begins a quest that will take her into the very heart of the Dreaming.
name: Weird Romance, Part One

description: Dark, nasty government forces conspire to hire Tommy. And they've convinced Green Lantern to help them out. How can Tommy sweet-talk a space-cop who can do nearly anything?
name: Local Hero, Part Three

description: An accidental death, a calculated murder, a kidnapping, a shopping spree for robots, and a hero on the highwire--the penultimate issue is jam-packed with excitement.
name: Episode Eight

description: Using his teleportation powers for the final time, Steel finds himself in a subterranean nightmare--trapped in a dank tunnel on what may or may not be Earth, confronted by a tentacled beast with a taste for metal.
name: The Thing

description: Between finding out his new girlfriend, Blaze Mancini, is the Democratic mayoral candidate's daughter and that his mysterious benefactor, the Colonel, wants him to keep the leader of the Three Fists triad alive, Cross's life has gotten quite a bit more complicated lately. And that was before stockbrokers started spontaneously combusting on the floor of the Exchange and supermodels turned assassin at the Spring fashion show!

Overview

"Stunning" . . . "incredible" . . . "an absolute must-buy" . . . these are just some of the words readers are using to describe Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER. And wait 'til they see the amazing fifth issue! In The Paradoxman, Tristan Caine's latest therapy session turns disturbingly ugly after he recounts the evolution of the TCI time chip and the resulting global war. In Young Gods, BWS himself steps on stage to interrupt the Gods' diversions of comet-counting and dragon-seeking after things get a bit out-of-hand. In The Freebooters, Axus the Great is in a grumpy mood brought on by an unwelcome guest, and his remedy is a call to action and adventure! The wit and artistry of Barry Windsor-Smith shift well into fifth gear in this incredible issue of this series!

OverviewThe Emerald of the Zuli is an immense gem with mind-controlling powers -- with that gem, a Nazi refugee controls his entire squad and the warrior women of Zuli, who, in their quest for purity, have unwittingly embraced the foul Nazi ideology. Deep within the jungles of upper Kenya, Tarzan must battle the magnificent female warriors as well as the squad of Nazis -- and all the odds are against him!
name: Legion of Hate (Part 2 of 4)

description: How is it that Usagi's lord was killed, leaving him a ronin? How did he receive the scar on his forehead? These questions and more are answered in this very special issue of Stan Sakai's Usagi Yojimbo, featuring three unique stories, including one inked by Sergio Aragones! Usagi's most popular villain -- Jei, the demon-possessed spearman -- continues his hunt for the rabbit ronin in the second story, and, in the third story, readers learn of what happens to a defeated general as he patiently waits for his chance to lead another rebellion . . . and what he does when his opportunity comes.
name: Return To Adachi Plain

description:
Overview
There came a time when there was great movement upon the earth and above it, when the destiny of men and gods was hammered out upon the forge of fate, when monstrous wars were brewed and mighty deeds were designed. And there rose up in this time, which was called the age of the Young Kingdoms, heroes. Greatest of these heroes was a doom-driven adventurer who bore a crooning runeblade that he loathed. His name was Elric of Melniboné...king of ruins...lord of a scattered race that had once ruled the world.
name: Dead God's Homecoming

description:
Someone is robbing the graves of Gotham City and Batman must discover who--and why--before it's too late.

A man calling himself the Undertaker began robbing graves and sending "Thank You" notes to the corpses' living relatives. The robbed graves led Batman to the funeral parlor that buried each victim. Batman took down the third generation mortician who was making a sculpture from the bones.
name: Boneyard Blues

description: Robin must go back to Halley's Circus to solve a disturbing string of crimes. Could star attraction Boston Brand--Deadman--be the cause?
name: Second Chances

description:
A Native American, Crazy Lightning, watches over a ghost town.

Two cowboys come up and confront him, only to be cowed by Crazy Lightning's control of a posse of snakes. They are stuck in a repeated loop of a day. Crazy Lighting says they are doomed to continue until they learn history.

Tim, who has been walking through the desert since the events of last issue, comes upon Crazy Lightning and asks him to let the others go. He refuses, but they talk, since Tim is British and not related to the American settlers.

However, Tim doesn't take him seriously, and Crazy Lightning turns into a giant snake, and calls himself Grandfather. He bites Tim, and says he'll die unless Tim is properly respectful. Tim calls him Grandfather and he bites him again, curing him. However, it also makes Tim grow a snake skin and freeze up, connecting with his "inner snake," as Grandfather tells him to consider how life is a cycle.

Tim sheds his skin and wakes up. Tim now feels more relaxed, and more in touch with nature. He is now able to dodge Grandfather's strikes.

Grandfather says he is the ghost of everything that died in the area from someone else's ego. He coalesced when a movie company set up a town to make cowboy films, which were even more disregarding of Natives than the real cowboys.

But, he wants to let them go, too, so he deputizes Tim to see if any of them care about anything besides themselves. Tim is soon set upon by the town roughs, but he magically takes their guns away.

However, Tim is indeed unable to find any worth in the settlers, and returns to Grandfather. They talk some more, and then Tim goes on his way.
name: Rites of Passage, Part Seven: Purgatory Creek - Population 1

description: The Challengers are called to Harvest, Wyoming to investigate a string of mysterious disappearances dating back to the 19th century.
name: Are You Ready for the Truth?

description: Asked by the city fathers to leave Keystone City and take the destruction of his super-heroic presence with him, Wally heads west to sunny California and the town of Santa Marta, which can't wait to claim the Flash as its resident super-hero. But Linda Park isn't willng to uproot her entire life & career to follow Wally to his new hometown.
name: Running Away From Home

description: A trail of murder and deceit leads to Kyle Rayner. Now, Green Lantern must set out to solve the crime that has left a long time GL cast member at death's door.
name: Retribution part 1

description: Kyle "Green Lantern" Rayner and Wally "Flash" West must team up to rescue their Golden Age counterparts (Alan Scott and Jay Garrick) from aliens who have abducted them.

"Last Man Standing" part 1! Drake's drum beats again--ringing out across the land and signaling great danger on the horizon for England. When Myrddin returns to modern day, the Knights of Arthur's court must seek out their champion!
name: Last Man Standing, Part 1 - A Different Kind Of Tension

description: Does Max have a deadly secret that threatens his and Bart's life? Impulse enlists Jesse Quick's aid in tracking Max on a cross-country run to learn the truth!
name: Played

description: Final issue! The answers Metron seeks lie beyond the impenetrable Source Wall. So he travels to this place of mystery to learn the fates of Highfather, Darkseid…and the future of the New Gods!
name: Closing The Ring

description:
Deep in the dungeons of Masada, something spooky is stirring. Elsewhere, Allfather D'Aronique reveals his master plan, Jesse hears the worst news in the world, and Starr gets just the first installment of what he so richly deserves.

Jesse makes it to Masada; Starr is found out by the Allfather, and tries to bring Jesse into his plan; the Saint of Killers arrives, and Hell follows with him.
name: Iron In The Blood (Crusaders Part 4)

description: As Wesley Dodds races to prove the innocence of Polish pilot Janos Prohaska--known as the high-flying Blackhawk--another murder is committed, one that enrages the European Resistance!
name: The Blackhawk: Act III of IV

description: "Patriots." Part 14 of 14. The National Interest use the American talisman to create their embodiment of the American Dream, the American Scream. But it may have met its match when it meets the Spectre and his ally, the talisman-created embodiment of America's hopes and dreams, The Patriot.
name: The Haunting of America - Conclusion: Patriots

description:
It's the Christmas season and the O'Dares host a holiday dinner. Many familiar faces appear, but a wayward Santa Claus delays Jack Knight's attendance in this standalone holiday issue.

Christmas at the O'dares. Jack is on his way, cut comes across a down-on-his-luck department store Santa. As the O'dares, Charity, Ted, Mikaal and even The Shade gather; Jack and Santa spread the holiday spirit and clean up the alleys of Opal on their way.
name: Christmas Knight

description: Normally the Man of Steel tries to prevent destruction, but when a pair of criminals attack him with a device created by Lex Luthor, Superman suddenly finds that the situation just got a lot heavier as his personal gravity increases to uncontrollable proportions!
name: Eye to Eye

description: Continuing the stunning Elseworlds miniseries featuring Robin and Batgirl: The pair continues to battle the corrupt criminal system in Gotham City. Unfortunately, their seemingly carefree adventures come to an abrupt halt when the Joker pieces together the clues to their true identities. Laying her trap, the Joker draws an injured Dick Grayson out of hiding using his family as bait.
name: Thrillkiller

description: The Cheetah's back, more feral, more ferocious than ever from her deal with Neron in UNDERWORLD UNLEAASHED. But her heightened powers are costing her her humanity and it's up to Wonder Woman to help her counter her deal with the devil and regain what she's lost.
name: Claws

description: As the battle rages between two of Marvel and DCs most powerful teams can Access unite the X-Men and the JLA to stop the real threat
name: Savior

description: Brainiape causes Hellboy to do battle with The Dragon, and then summons a giant sea monster, which eats them both. Unaffected by the Vampire's bite, Cyberface is only restored to health after Abner Cadaver imbues him with the life force of those around him. Hellboy's government allies kill the sea monster, and the emerging Dragon impales Brainiape's brain with a knife, freeing Hellboy from his mental control.

Eddie and Andy, the abused children who killed their father, escape their detention and find their way to New York City in search of their hero, Spawn. There, they are befriended by Snake who offers to employ Eddie to courier illegal packages for him. Snake forces Eddie to lead him to Spawn where a confrontation ensues. Snake is killed and Andy is wounded. After medical treatment, the boys return to the detention center, forever stripped of their innocence.
name: Orphans

description: The mysterious mystical entity known as The Architect opens a competition for hired mercenaries and assassins.
name: A Little Piece of Paradise

description:
Emma Frost, Paige Guthrie, Monet St. Croix and Jubilee Lee spend Christmas Eve in M’s Monaco home. Throughout the evening, they bond whilst telling each other previously untold stories of the first manifestation of their powers.   
Jubilee had been shoplifting at a mall, but when cornered by the police, she set off her fireworks to cover her escape. 
M fabricates a tale in which her family were thrilled to witness her powers.  As she finishes, Emplate's astral form appears and puts the others in stasis, while he begs Monet to free him from the dimension in which he is trapped.  She refuses and he fades away. 
Paige relates how, once her brother, Sam, exhibited his powers, she wished and prayed she, too, would be a mutant.  After some time, she got what she wanted. 
Emma, commited to an asylum by her parents, discovered her ability to control others there, and used her powers, first to escape, then later, to build her financial empire.
Back at Xavier's School, Black Tom Cassidy meets with Mondo and prepares to make his move.
name: Home for the Holidays

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

name: Hurray for Hulk; A Little Leeway

description: Roxxon Oil is causing trouble in the Savage Land again.
name: A Savage Land
Back in Business

description:
Background

This issue is the origin of Christopher Pike's five year mission. The whole story takes place before the pilot episode of the Original Series. It introduces the whole crew of the U.S.S. Enterprise. All the main characters are there from the original pilot with the exception of Mia Colt. She did not become Captain Pike's Yeoman until later in the mission so she is unseen here. There are also a bunch of new characters that were never a part of the series.

Summary

The Crew face a giant space creature that plans to use the crew as scraps for it's own purpose. It is very similar to the Borg making them a part of themselves to make them better. They have already taken over many smaller ships and the Enterprise could be the very next victim.
name: Flesh of My Flesh

description: A wicked battle with a Kazon warship leaves Voyager in desperate need of repairs. But when Voyager limps off to the planet Praja, they find it barren, stripped of all life! What gives?
name: Homeostasis, Part One
